    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      After doing a competitive analysis and doing some researches on this project, we started working on wireframes. This phase took a lot of time because feasibility is one of the biggest problems for us to consider. After talking with the team and engineer, we got lots of reviews and updates. They gave us a new aspect to think about this feature.
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      The three versions have solid pros and cons. For version #1 and version #2, we didn 't separate the city picking process. We thought it is easier for users to select all the cities that they would like to go at the same time. Since our algorithm requires an actual date to generate trip literature,  the process of date picking is essential.  We tested and evaluated version #1 and version #2. We found out that it simplified the process, but so many changes for the flow would increase and delay the time to launch our App.  So version # 3 is more suitable at this point to achieve the goals.

section(id='final-design' class="container-fluid")
  div(class="section-wrapper row justify-content-md-center")
    h2(class='section-title col-lg-8 col-md-10') FINAL DESIGN
    div(class='gray-bg container-fluid')
      div(data-toggle="modal"
          data-target="#finalModalImg"
          class='row .ver-hor-center justify-content-md-center')
        div(class='col-lg-12 ver-hor-center')
          img(src="/public/assets/finalD_2.png", alt="")
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      We are giving options to select the same city more than one time.
      Therefore, there is no need to select the home city and the return city.
      The first and the last city on the card will be the start and end city.
      So the "+" button will not change,
      no matter how many times the same city has been added.
      The system will generate a plan based on the order of the cities.
      In that case, users can arrange the orders freely by their needs.
    p(class='col-lg-8 col-md-10').
      Our goal is to make the process simple and more intuitive for the user to start plan.
      After clicking on the "+" button on the city cart,
      the calendar will pop-up directly. After a city selected,
      the cart icon will be colored to show there is something added.

